2.speaker: POLAR BEAR
2.character: おはよう　パンダくん

3.speaker: PANDA
3.character: あれ！？　これ　なんの荷物？

4.speaker: POLAR BEAR
4.definition: I'm getting ready for a trip.

5.speaker: PANDA
5.character: えっ！？　出かけちゃうの？ カフェは？
5.definition: You're going on a trip? What about the café?

6.speaker: POLAR BEAR
6.definition: It's closed for the day. What?

7.speaker: PANDA
7.character: せっかく　早起きできたからモーニング食べようと思ったのに
7.definition: But I got up early, so I figured I could make it in time for breakfast.

11.speaker: GRIZZLY
11.character: シロクマ！ 用意はできてんだろうな？
11.definition: You better be ready, Polar Bear.

14.speaker: PANDA
14.character: グリズリーさんおはよう

16.speaker: PANDA
16.character: シロクマくんとどこ行くの？
16.definition: Where are you two headed? We're gonna go get some ingredients.

17.speaker: POLAR BEAR
17.character: 料理の材料を発掘しに
17.definition: We're going to go excavate for some ingredients for cooking.

19.speaker: PANDA
19.definition: I wanna go, too. This ain't no game!

20.speaker: POLAR BEAR
20.character: まぁ　でも 遠足みたいなものかな
20.definition: Well, it is sort of like a field trip.

22.speaker: PANDA
22.character: 笹はおやつに入る？ ごはんかな？
22.definition: Will there be bamboo grass for snacks? Or maybe lunch?

24.speaker: POLAR BEAR
24.character: アザラシはごはんだけど…

26.speaker: POLAR BEAR
26.definition: Maybe walruses. What the hell are you babbling about?

27.definition: Let's go! Hurry and get in!

29.speaker: POLAR BEAR
29.character: 何？　グリズリーくん

30.speaker: GRIZZLY
30.character: なんでアイツがいるんだよ？
30.definition: Why the hell is he here? You told him to get in.

31.speaker: GRIZZLY
31.definition: That's not what I meant! It doesn't really matter.

33.character: 山？　それとも　海？
33.definition: To the mountains? Or maybe to the beach?

34.speaker: PANDA
34.character: 山はおいしい笹がいっぱい生えてるし…
34.definition: There's lots of delicious bamboo grass in the mountains.

35.speaker: PANDA
35.character: 海はかわいい女の子がいっぱいいるよね
35.definition: And there're a lot of cute girls at the beach.

37.speaker: GRIZZLY
37.character: お前は店で出す分が欲しいんだろ？
37.definition: You want some for your café, right?

38.speaker: POLAR BEAR
38.character: うん　いっぱい獲れるといいな
38.definition: Yup. It'd be great if we catch get a lot.

39.speaker: GRIZZLY
39.character: 結構いそうな感じだぜ
39.definition: It looks like there's quite a few.

41.speaker: GRIZZLY
41.character: あれが俺たちの獲物だ
41.definition: That would be our target. That?

43.speaker: GRIZZLY
43.definition: What? I was imagining something more like bamboo shoots.

44.speaker: GRIZZLY
44.definition: If you don't want any, go home!

45.speaker: PANDA
45.character: なんだ…　発掘じゃないじゃない
45.definition: This isn't an excavation at all.

46.speaker: POLAR BEAR
46.character: 似たようなもんでしょ

49.speaker: POLAR BEAR
49.character: 明日からのしろくまカフェのランチ
49.definition: Starting tomorrow, lunch at Polar Bear's Café

50.speaker: POLAR BEAR
50.character: グリズリー君にかかってるんだから
50.definition: is all riding on you, Grizzly.

51.speaker: GRIZZLY
51.character: まったく…　他力本願なヤツめ
51.definition: Jeez, relying on me to do all your work.

52.speaker: PANDA
52.character: えっ　どうやって獲るの？
52.definition: Ooh, how's he going to catch it?

55.speaker: GRIZZLY
55.character: まぁ　俺の手にかかりゃ こんなもんよ

57.speaker: PANDA
57.character: わぁ…　ピチピチしてる
57.definition: They're wiggling around. I faced a situation like this as a kid, too...

59.speaker: GRIZZLY
59.definition: I can't catch any of them.

60.speaker: GRIZZLY
60.character: なんだシロクマ！　テメエ！ 笑って見てんじゃねえ！
60.definition: What the hell's your problem, Polar Bear?! Don't stand there laughing!

62.speaker: GRIZZLY
62.character: 笑ってるだろうが　口がよ！

63.speaker: POLAR BEAR
63.character: 口の下が黒いだけだよ
63.definition: It's just that my bottom lip is black.

64.speaker: GRIZZLY
64.character: ホントだ　口　閉じてる
64.definition: You're right, your mouth is closed.

66.speaker: GRIZZLY
66.character: やっぱ　笑ってんじゃねえか！
66.definition: You are laughing, you ass! Couldn't help it.

67.speaker: GRIZZLY
67.character: アイツに笑われてた俺も
67.definition: He may have been laughing then,

68.character: 今じゃ　立派にサケが獲れるようになったんだぜ
68.definition: but I can catch salmon like no other now. What the hell are you doing? {eh?} Getting ready for a picnic.

69.speaker: GRIZZLY
69.character: 俺が働いてるときに何だそりゃ！
69.definition: What the hell are you doing while I'm doing all the work?!

70.speaker: POLAR BEAR
70.character: まぁまぁ　グリズリーくんがサケ獲って お腹が空いたら
70.definition: Now, now, when you get hungry from catching all the salmon,

71.speaker: POLAR BEAR
71.character: ランチができてるってわけ
71.definition: I'll have lunch ready for you.

72.speaker: POLAR BEAR
72.character: なかなか　いいでしょ

73.speaker: GRIZZLY
73.character: 腹にたまるもんを頼むぜ
73.definition: Make something that'll fill me up. There aren't any salmon. What the hell are you doing?!

74.speaker: PANDA
74.character: なかなか グリズリーさんみたいにはいかないね
74.definition: I can't seem to get the hang of it like you, Mr. Grizzly. It totally looked like anyone could do it.

75.speaker: GRIZZLY
75.character: いいか　よく見てろ
75.definition: Jeez, watch closely. This is how it's—

76.speaker: PANDA
76.character: もういいや　笹食べよっと
76.definition: I'm done. I'm gonna go eat bamboo grass.

77.speaker: GRIZZLY
77.character: そんな簡単に諦めんな！
77.definition: Don't wuss out so easily! But I'm tired, and I'm hungry.

78.speaker: GRIZZLY
78.character: そういう問題じゃねえ！

79.speaker: GRIZZLY
79.character: 同じクマとして　シロクマ！お前もコイツに何か言ってやれ！
79.definition: You're a bear, too, Polar Bear! Talk to him!

80.speaker: POLAR BEAR
80.character: パンダくんは 竹と笹があれば満足だから
80.definition: Panda is happy if he has his bamboo and bamboo grass.

83.speaker: GRIZZLY
83.character: クマは狩りだろ 狩ってこそのクマだろ！
83.definition: If you're a bear, hunt! Hunting is what makes you a bear!

85.speaker: POLAR BEAR
85.character: ちょっとそこでとってきた

86.speaker: POLAR BEAR
86.character: これだったら　パンダくんも狩りをする気になるでしょ
86.definition: This will probably make Panda want to hunt, too.

88.speaker: PANDA
88.character: えっ　サケってタケノコ食べるの？

90.speaker: GRIZZLY
90.character: お前が食うんだよ　パンダ
90.definition: You're going to eat it, Panda.

92.speaker: POLAR BEAR
92.character: グリズリーくんが 狩りのお手本見せてくれるって
92.definition: Grizzly's going to show you how to hunt.

93.speaker: POLAR BEAR
93.character: 狩りをしてこそのクマだもんね
93.definition: Hunting is what makes you a bear, right? Y-Yeah! Watch closely, Panda.

94.speaker: POLAR BEAR
94.character: まずは　標的を見つける

95.speaker: POLAR BEAR
95.definition: Don't ever take your eyes off of it.

96.speaker: POLAR BEAR
96.character: 獲物の動きを予測する
96.definition: Predict how your enemy will move.

97.speaker: GRIZZLY
97.character: どうだ　やってみろ
97.definition: How's that? Now you do it.

99.speaker: GRIZZLY
99.character: って食ってんじゃねえ！

100.speaker: GRIZZLY
100.character: ちゃんと泳いでるタケノコをとれ
100.definition: Come catch the swimming bamboo shoot!

101.speaker: POLAR BEAR
101.character: タケノコは泳がないよ

104.speaker: PANDA
104.character: イライラしないで　グリズリーさん
104.definition: Don't be so mad, Mr. Grizzly.

105.speaker: PANDA
105.character: 僕のとっておきの笹あげるから
105.definition: I'll give you my best bamboo grass.

106.speaker: PANDA
106.character: 笹は健康にもいいんだよ
106.definition: It's really good for your health, too.

107.speaker: GRIZZLY
107.character: お前も食わず嫌いしてないで
107.definition: Don't be a picky eater yourself, and eat some salmon. Okay.

109.speaker: GRIZZLY
109.character: あんまし　うまくねえ
109.definition: Not that good. Isn't the salmon better? Not really.

115.speaker: PANDA
115.character: いっぱいとれてよかったね
115.definition: It's good that you caught so much.

117.speaker: GRIZZLY
117.character: おい　パンダ！　こっちだ

119.speaker: SASAKO
119.character: おかげさまで大人気ですよ　ランチパスタ
119.definition: The lunch pasta is a hit, thanks to you.

123.speaker: POLAR BEAR
123.definition: It's for all your hard work yesterday.

124.speaker: GRIZZLY
124.character: おい　パンダ　俺のタケノコお前にやる
124.definition: Hey, Panda, I'll give you my bamboo shoots. I'll give you my salmon, Mr. Grizzly.

125.speaker: SASAKO
125.character: あ　好き嫌いはダメですよ
125.definition: It's not good to be such picky eaters.

126.speaker: GRIZZLY
126.character: 細かいこと気にするなよ

129.speaker: PANDA
129.character: ペンギンさん　ペンギンさん

130.speaker: PENGUIN
130.definition: What is it, Panda? Please tell me all the life lessons you have learned so far.

131.speaker: PENGUIN
131.character: 飲み会で最後に残った一個を食べる時は
131.definition: When you're out drinking with others, and you're trying to eat the last piece,

132.speaker: PENGUIN
132.character: お皿を下げてもらうどさくさで食べちゃえば
132.definition: if you try to eat it as they're taking the plate,

134.speaker: PANDA
134.character: 心の底から小さい知恵だね
134.definition: That is a truly shallow life lesson.

136.speaker: POLAR BEAR
136.definition: Next time, on Polar Bear's Café Z.
